review_blob: On tap. Pours is cloudy amber with thick white head. Aroma rather malty, some fruity hops, light pine and resin. Taste is light sweet, moderate bitter, resiny mouthfeel. Light to medium body, sticky texture, bitter finish.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Bottle. Pours is cloudy orange with medium white head. Sweet aroma of wheat, banana, peach. Taste is moderate to medium sweet, fruity mouthfeel. Medium body, sticky texture, fruity sweet finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark ruby with very thick reddish head that lasts only for seconds. Funky, leather, cherry, wet leaves. Taste is light sweet with some acidic notes, cherries on tongue. Light body, thick texture, fruity fresh finish.

Bottle. Pours is cloudy pale with thick white head. Aroma of citruses, tangerine, lemon, orange. Taste is light sweet, moderate bitter, citrusy mouthfeel. Light body, soft carbonation, slick texture, light bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark with thick brown head. Aroma of plums, figues, smoked cheese, dark chocolate. Taste is medium sweet, light salty, smoked cheese on tongue, fruity. Medium to heavy body, sticky texture, flat carbonation, light smokey finish. Overally good, I like the presence of fruity taste but its just too much.

Bottle. Pours is dark with thick brown head. Sweet aroma of fruits, liquorice, plums, chocolate, coffee, very inviting. Taste is light sweet, light bitter, dry, coffee and chocolate mouthfeel. Heavy body, creamy texture, coffee bitter finish.

On tap. Pours is clear amber with thick stable off-white head, leaves lacing. Aroma of caramel, biscuits, passion fruit, peach. Taste is light sweet, light bitter, caramel on tongue. Medium body, sticky texture, light bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is cloudy orange with thick stable white head. Aroma of wheat, spices, licorice, ginger. Taste is moderate sweet, citrusy fresh with just a touch of licorice. Medium body, creamy texture.
beer_name: To l Wit Is The New Black

review_blob: On tap. Pours is cloudy orange with thick white head. Aroma of rye, caramel, grapes, raisins, touch of resin. Taste is light to moderate sweet, light bitter, rye mouthfeel. Medium body, sticky texture, light bitter finish.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is clear golden with thick white head, leaves lacing. Aroma is floral, citrusy, strawy. Taste goes from light sweet to light bitter, malty mouthfeel. Light body, soft carbonation, sticky texture, light bitter finish

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is clear golden with thick white head. Harsh aroma of pine and resin. Taste is light sweet, medium to heavy bitter, resiny notes. Medium body, sticky texture, bitter finish. Drinkable but far away from what I consider a ballanced beer.

Bottle. Pours is cloudy amber with very thick white head. Aroma of caramel, resin, wheat, grapes, fruity. Solid malty base, moderate sweet, bitter notes, caramel, resin, wheat on tongue. Heavy body, oily, smooth texture, soft carbonation, medium dry, light bitter finish. Well hidden alcohol, incredibly smooth.

Bottle. Pours is golden clear with thick stable white head. Aroma of orange and tangerine, yeast, spices, floral. Taste is light to moderate sweet, moderate bitter, heavy malty base with citrusy and floral mouthfeel. Heavy body, oily to creamy texture, soft carbonation, light bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is cloudy golden with medium stable white head. Aroma of wheat, yeast, spices, clove, ginger. Taste is medium sweet, moderate bitter, lot of yeast on tongue. Medium body, creamy texture, lively carbonation.
On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Aroma of citruses, lemon, tangerine, wheat, floral. Taste is light sweet, medium bitter, citrusy mouthfeel. Light body, soft carbonation, bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark with thick brown head that lasts for few seconds. Aroma of roasted malts, dark chocolate, cocoa, touch of coffee, light nuts. Heavy malty base, light sweet taste, light bitter, dry, coffee mouthfeel. Heavy body, oily texture, soft carbonation, coffee and chocolate finish. Nicely ballanced, well hidden alcohol.

Bottle. Pours is clear orange with thick white head. Aroma of tropical fruits, passion fruit, grapefruit, resin, tangerine. Taste is light fruity sweet, moderate to medium bitter, tropical fruity mouthfeel. Medium body, oily texture, soft carbonation, long bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is cloudy orange to light amber with very thick white head. Aroma of tea, cherry, resin, touch of tangerine and lime. Taste goes from moderate/ medium finish to heavy dry, tea aftertaste. Medium body, sticky texture, soft carbonation, bitter finish. Extraordinary, I cant really decide if I like it or if I hate it.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is clear golden with big white head, leaves lacing. Aroma is malty, spicy, touch of caramel. Taste is light sweet, moderate bitter, caramel and malts on tongue. Medium body, oily texture, flat carbonation, light bitter finish.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is clear orange with thick white head. Sweet aroma of pine, resin, fruity. Taste is light sweet, medium bitter, solid malty base, resiny mouthfeel. Heavy body, oily texture, ling heavy bitter finish.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is clear golden with thick white head. Aroma is fruity, apricot, peach, light lemon, light straw. Taste is a bit harsh, dry, moderate bitter, almost abruptly bitter. Medium body, sticky texture, bitter finish. Nice but a bit unballanced.

Bottle. Pours is cloudy orange with thick white head. Aroma of orange peel, grapefruit, tangerine, touch of tropical fruits. Taste is light sweet, medium to heavy bitter, citrusy mouthfeel. Medium body, sticky texture, bitter finish.

beer_name: Bevog Who Cares Editions Double IPA (Shower Beer)

review_blob: On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is red/amber clear with medium reddish head, leaves lacing. Aroma of raspberries, sirup, light malts, barnyard. Taste is fruity sweet, sirupy, raspberries. Medium body, oily to sticky texture, flat carbonation, fruity aftertaste.

.On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is cloudy orange with medium white head. Aroma of pine, light resin, light orange. Taste is light to moderate bitter, orange and malty background, rather citric fruity. Medium body, slick to sticky texture, light bitter finish.
Can. Pours is clear goldeb with medium foamy white head. Aroma of malts, grain, bread, grass. Taste is moderate bitter, strawy mouthfeel. Medium body, sticky texture, bitter finish.

Bottle. Poura is clear dark amber with medium beige creamy head that lasts for long time. Aroma of smoked malts, smoked cheese, plums, fruity touch. Taste is light bitter, dry, light fruity sweetnes, lot of smoke notes in tongue. Light to medium body, slick to creamy texture, very dry, coffee bittery finish.

beer_brewer_name: Pivovar a plenica Turk a vnuk

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is orange cloudy with thick white head. Aroma of tangerine, orange peel, lime. Taste is light sweet, moderate bitter, orange mouthfeel. Light to medium body, slick texture, light bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark with thick brown head. Aroma of citruses, lemon, tangerine. Taste is moderate bitter, roasty malts on tongue. Medium body, slick texture, coffee bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark with medium brown head. Aroma of roasted malts, milk chocolate, hazelnuts. Taste is light sweet, malty. Medium body, slick texture, lot of milk chocolate on tongue. Great.

Bottle. Pours is dark brown with very thick tan head. Aroma of hazelnuts, roasted malts, toffee, touch of fruits and citruses. Taste is light sweet, moderate to medium bitter, hazelnuts on tongue. Light to medium body, sticky texture, long heavy bitter finish.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is dark, with thick creamy beige head. Aroma of pine, resin, roasted malts. Taste is light sweet, moderate bitter, roasty and resiny mouthfeel. Medium body, sticky texture, coffee bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark with thick tan head. Aroma of roasted malts, pine, resin, fruity. Taste is moderate to medium bitter, lot of roasted malts on tongue. Medium body, sticky texture, roasty bitter finish.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is orange clear with medium creamy white head. Aroma of straw, cheese, not very inviting. Taste is moderate bitter. Medium body, thick texture, bitter finish.

Bottle. Pours is dark brown with big tan head, fair lacing. Aroma is malty, dried fruits, plums, cinammon, spices. Taste is light sweet, moderate bitter with some acidic notes, malty mouthfeel. Medium body, sticky texture, malty aftertaste.

Bottle. Pours is light clear amber with very thick head. Aroma of caramel, biscuits, pine, heavy herbal. Moderate to medium bitter, caramel and pine mouthfeel. Medium body, oily texture, soft carbonation, bitter finish. Aroma was pretty weak but taste was very good, overally nice and drinkable beer.

On tap at na 7.schode, Zilina. Pours is cloudy golden with almost no head. Aroma of hops orange, tangerine, floral, juicy. Taste is light sweet, light to moderate sour, marmalade fruity mouthfeel. Medium body, heavy oily texture, flat carbonation, light acidic finish. Awesomely ballanced, juicy fresh beer.
